reviewText: I enjoyed this wonderful little story, although the events were from a dog's point of view. The Iditerod is the race that was run from Nenana to Nome in order to bring medicine to Nome to combat a Diptheria Outbreak. Balto did finish the race, so that much was true. In this tale Balto is an underdog who is ostrasized because he is half wolf. With a Russian Goose as his mentor and friend and two polar bears who cannot swim, Balto sets off to prove that he is capable of being a sled dog when the team gets lost and leads the team home.In Wolf Quest, he and his young daughter follow a raven to a more spiritual journey to help a pack of wolves facing starvation to seek a way to reach the Caribou that have gone over pack ice to reach a far shore and both soon learn where they actually belong. I love the double pack as it cuts down on space and yet allows both movies to be enjoyed as they are.
summary: Not Disney, but pretty good nonetheless....
